01:17.829 --> 01:20.873
Anyway, I heard her say she has a bookstore
on Bleecker in the Village.

01:21.332 --> 01:25.503
Gonna find her, gonna make her tell us
what Maggie and Pete are really up to.

01:27.338 --> 01:28.715
Grandpa and Sam lied to me.

01:29.716 --> 01:30.758
Lied about what?

01:31.009 --> 01:33.136
What happened to Mum and Dad,
the accident.

01:34.304 --> 01:36.180
They told me that they
were hit by some drunk

01:36.222 --> 01:39.058
but Taylor said that the police report
didn't mention the guy was drunk.

01:39.726 --> 01:41.519
And then they said,
"Well, maybe the cop made a mistake."

01:41.561 --> 01:42.687
but I could tell they were lying.

01:42.812 --> 01:45.565
Well, my guess is that your grandpa
and Sam were drunk themselves.

01:46.399 --> 01:50.320
The man who killed Lila and Danny
may or may not have been drunk

01:50.403 --> 01:51.487
but he was a drunk.

01:52.196 --> 01:53.406
Jacques Reynard.

01:54.824 --> 01:57.994
His family came down from Quebec
a few generations back.

01:58.661 --> 02:00.121
Strong Catholics, good people.

02:00.788 --> 02:01.914
Until Jacques.

02:03.207 --> 02:05.543
Pardon my French,
but he was a mean motherfucker.

02:23.645 --> 02:24.646
There you go.

02:26.230 --> 02:27.523
She didn't call or text?

02:28.816 --> 02:30.360
I think she picked up my tail.

02:31.277 --> 02:34.489
She slowed down when she came by here,
but then kept going.

02:36.407 --> 02:37.283
There you go.

02:42.622 --> 02:43.748
What do you want, Sean?

02:46.793 --> 02:47.919
I never thanked you.

02:48.628 --> 02:49.712
Thanked me for what?

02:49.962 --> 02:51.631
The firecrackers in my locker

02:53.091 --> 02:54.967
the roaches in my gym clothes

02:55.885 --> 02:58.930
the name calling, the threats

03:00.473 --> 03:02.350
the fucking crayfish.

03:02.767 --> 03:03.810
We were kids.

03:04.435 --> 03:06.354
Did you know crayfish feel pain?

03:08.147 --> 03:09.190
- No.
- Oh.

03:09.565 --> 03:10.441
True fact.

03:12.235 --> 03:14.946
But their shells get tougher because of it.

03:15.780 --> 03:16.989
You see where I'm going with this?

03:18.700 --> 03:19.867
You're the fucking crayfish.

03:20.076 --> 03:21.285
- Exactly.
- Mm.

03:21.411 --> 03:25.873
And all of the "practical jokes"
you and your fucking cousin played on me

03:27.083 --> 03:28.292
just made me stronger.

03:31.754 --> 03:34.841
I thought maybe you came here
to talk about Shannon.

03:36.384 --> 03:37.260
In a minute.

03:38.428 --> 03:41.264
I just wanna savour this,
cos almost 20 years later

03:41.347 --> 03:44.183
one of us is the CEO
of a successful business

03:44.267 --> 03:45.977
pulling out a half mil a year

03:47.353 --> 03:49.230
and one of us is a fucking cop.

03:51.816 --> 03:52.942
You're banging her, right?

03:57.572 --> 03:58.781
Simple question.

04:00.450 --> 04:02.493
Are you banging my wife?

04:05.079 --> 04:05.955
Yeah.

04:18.176 --> 04:19.594
Better you than me at this point.

04:21.220 --> 04:25.683
I was into her once,
but you eat filet mignon every night

04:25.767 --> 04:28.186
you kinda lose your taste for it, you know?

04:29.729 --> 04:31.564
She should've left you a long time ago.

04:32.106 --> 04:33.107
Was that the plan?

04:34.317 --> 04:37.487
Wait for the Hartford deal to go through,
and then split, take half?

04:38.404 --> 04:39.447
Yeah, I figured.

04:41.532 --> 04:43.659
You should tell her to take a look
at the paperwork

04:43.701 --> 04:45.745
I signed when I took over from Daddy.

04:48.247 --> 04:50.082
Since you didn't go to
college, I'll explain.

04:50.875 --> 04:53.419
ANB is now a separate entity

04:54.045 --> 04:55.963
what we call a holding company

04:56.714 --> 05:01.177
and as such is not subject
to community property statutes.

05:02.970 --> 05:06.557
I can't really see Shannon living off
a cop's salary, can you?

05:09.936 --> 05:11.270
It's not just about the money.

05:12.188 --> 05:15.107
What, you know what they say
about love and money, don't you?

05:15.858 --> 05:19.320
When you say you want both,
you really just want the money.

05:23.324 --> 05:25.409
AJ, how far can you snake the tube?

05:25.660 --> 05:28.079
According to the blueprint,
I only have to go 20 yards.

05:30.581 --> 05:33.793
Are you gonna keep doing this Henry
the Five checking-on-his-troops routine

05:33.876 --> 05:35.127
or are you gonna lend a hand?

05:35.294 --> 05:36.879
"We few, we happy few."

05:36.963 --> 05:37.839
I'm not happy.

05:39.924 --> 05:41.467
Is this gonna be ready by noon tomorrow?

05:42.552 --> 05:46.013
Not having an actual slot to test it on,
your guess is as good as mine.

05:46.681 --> 05:47.598
That's not true.

05:47.974 --> 05:49.058
My guess isn't a guess.

05:50.101 --> 05:51.394
How loud is it gonna be?

05:52.270 --> 05:53.938
You mean as measured on a decibel scale?

05:54.313 --> 05:58.401
Let's see, uh, lawnmower's 90 decibels,
jet engine is 120

05:58.568 --> 06:01.779
hearing damage can occur at 85 decibels,
gunshots are 140.

06:02.363 --> 06:03.698
This'll be about...

06:08.286 --> 06:09.161
That work?

06:09.453 --> 06:12.248
- What is his problem?
- Lack of friends.

06:13.457 --> 06:15.126
I thought you were headed to the casino.

06:15.835 --> 06:16.711
Soon.

06:17.086 --> 06:18.045
What name do you want?

06:18.087 --> 06:20.006
Something that you forget
a second after you hear it.

06:22.383 --> 06:23.759
Eleven million is a lot of money.

06:25.011 --> 06:26.470
You sure you know what you're in for?

06:26.888 --> 06:28.806
I'm in for $11 million. What about you?

06:30.016 --> 06:31.100
I'm doing it for her.

06:34.729 --> 06:35.688
What, Maggie?

06:37.356 --> 06:38.608
I had my shot at big money.

06:39.692 --> 06:41.360
My tribe was gonna build a casino.

06:41.986 --> 06:43.321
I saw nothing but trouble.

06:43.905 --> 06:46.532
My son saw only dollars.

06:48.534 --> 06:49.785
What happened to the casino?

06:50.328 --> 06:51.370
Council voted for it.

06:51.537 --> 06:53.539
Then members of the tribe started
getting kicked out.

06:54.373 --> 06:56.500
Fewer members meant more money
for those who remain.

06:58.753 --> 06:59.879
It never got built.

07:01.005 --> 07:02.965
And now I work for another tribe's casino.

07:04.133 --> 07:05.176
Gotta get to work.

07:07.803 --> 07:09.013
You guys best friends now?

07:10.264 --> 07:12.308
Kwahu was your cut-out, wasn't he?

07:13.476 --> 07:16.354
He's how you and Pete communicated
when you were on the run.

07:16.896 --> 07:19.482
I've known Kwahu since I was 14 years old.

07:20.149 --> 07:22.818
Dad used to take me with him
if he had a client on the reserve.

07:23.152 --> 07:25.404
Let me guess, he...
he understood your gifts.

07:26.781 --> 07:28.574
No, he had the best weed.

07:36.457 --> 07:38.125
Julia, hi.

07:38.834 --> 07:40.628
No, Sam and I have been to Luis' place.

07:40.795 --> 07:43.130
<i>He wasn't there.
So much for taking the hit off Valerie.</i>

07:43.756 --> 07:45.758
I know. He's with Dockery.

07:46.258 --> 07:49.178
I'm out of leverage,
and now Ayawamat is hunting for me.

07:49.553 --> 07:50.888
Sam and I will come and get ya.

07:51.097 --> 07:53.891
No, no, no, I'm fine, but can you pick up
Ellen and Jacob

07:53.933 --> 07:56.435
and take them to someone
completely unconnected to the family?

07:56.644 --> 07:58.813
<i>Well, yeah, sure,
but I'm worried about you.</i>

07:59.146 --> 08:01.899
Luis and Ayawamat, they're not gonna
stop looking for you.

08:02.108 --> 08:03.609
I got a place to lie low.

08:03.734 --> 08:05.486
Pretty sure no one'll think
to look for me here.

08:07.613 --> 08:08.489
Yeah.

09:51.592 --> 09:52.927
Hannah, baby.

09:53.761 --> 09:55.012
Come on, wake up.

09:55.387 --> 09:57.223
- I got your coffee.
- Just 30 minutes.

09:57.306 --> 09:59.558
No, no, not today.
You got make-up duty.

10:00.059 --> 10:01.560
What the hell are you talking about?

10:01.602 --> 10:03.354
Those two old fucks,
the ones you let into the house

10:03.395 --> 10:06.190
to steal the Proclamation?
You gotta make right.

10:06.982 --> 10:08.317
I need you to watch Valerie's house.

10:08.359 --> 10:10.528
Can't I just give you a handy or something?

10:11.237 --> 10:12.238
That's tempting, but no.

10:12.530 --> 10:14.281
- Come on.
- Can I have a gun?

10:15.324 --> 10:16.826
- You want my gun?
- Yeah.

10:16.951 --> 10:18.035
Mm, yeah.

10:18.077 --> 10:19.078
- Yeah?
- Mmm...

10:19.120 --> 10:21.914
- I wanna carry your gun.
- Oh, you wanna carry my gun?

10:22.039 --> 10:23.958
- I like your...
- Mmm.

10:40.808 --> 10:43.644
You know,
I'll be leaving for work soon.

10:43.894 --> 10:45.271
Do you need a ride?

10:49.150 --> 10:51.110
I'm not leaving until it's dark.

11:02.580 --> 11:03.914
Seriously?

11:09.712 --> 11:10.880
Fuck.

11:24.685 --> 11:25.561
Huh.

12:06.894 --> 12:07.811
Arnold.

12:13.108 --> 12:14.735
What was Suzanne so excited about?

12:14.902 --> 12:15.903
She got some great news.

12:18.072 --> 12:19.406
That's not great news.

12:21.158 --> 12:24.453
Um, uh... I don't know.
Yeah, I'll call you back.

12:26.080 --> 12:28.249
- Who was that?
- That was Kwahu.

12:28.707 --> 12:33.712
Uh, Suzanne, the casino manager,
she's having the buffalo authenticated

12:33.921 --> 12:35.130
by the Smithsonian.

12:35.339 --> 12:37.758
- When?
- Tomorrow at noon.

12:43.138 --> 12:44.265
So, this is what we have.

12:45.140 --> 12:46.892
Uh, they find out
that it's a regular buffalo

12:46.934 --> 12:50.229
they put it back in the museum,
we have to scrap everything and start over.

12:50.854 --> 12:53.190
That's the best-case scenario.

12:53.315 --> 12:56.777
The worst-case scenario
is that they find the $11 million

12:57.236 --> 12:59.530
and it's the biggest jackpot
the casino's ever had.

13:00.072 --> 13:01.407
There has to be another option.

13:05.953 --> 13:07.037
We go tonight.

13:09.873 --> 13:11.083
- Tonight?
- We go in

13:11.458 --> 13:14.003
with half a build and no rehearsal.

13:14.128 --> 13:15.796
We have to convince them, but I don't...

13:16.505 --> 13:21.260
Look, you're a professional,
and you've been doing this all your life

13:22.094 --> 13:24.430
and, uh, so has every member of your team.

13:24.471 --> 13:26.890
Right, so, but even if we were
gonna go in with half a build

13:26.932 --> 13:28.517
Suzanne's working tonight, right?

13:28.600 --> 13:31.520
And if she doesn't recognise me,
she's gonna recognise you and Gina.

13:31.562 --> 13:32.855
Then get her out of the picture.

13:33.397 --> 13:34.648
What's with all the confidence?

13:35.232 --> 13:39.778
Look, two days ago, you were in a car
on your way to die in a tub of acid

13:40.904 --> 13:41.905
and now, you're here.

13:42.614 --> 13:43.490
Hm?

13:56.712 --> 13:58.380
<i>- Katie?</i>
- I'm sorry

13:58.464 --> 14:01.717
but the number you've reached
no longer takes calls from con men

14:01.800 --> 14:03.218
looking to get out of trouble.

14:03.510 --> 14:05.846
$5,000, three hours, including travel.

14:05.888 --> 14:06.930
No guns, no nudity.

14:08.515 --> 14:09.933
- Tell me you don't need the money.
- Ugh...

14:09.975 --> 14:12.644
- What is it?
<i>- It's a 24-hour Montezuma.</i>

14:16.106 --> 14:17.566
Who, what, where, when?

14:17.608 --> 14:18.609
<i>It's the Mohegan Sun.</i>

14:18.650 --> 14:20.944
It's a casino manager,
you're a Hartford reporter

14:22.237 --> 14:23.655
and it has to be this afternoon.

14:24.448 --> 14:25.991
You provide the cocktail.

14:39.088 --> 14:41.548
Alright, change of plans.

14:43.384 --> 14:45.552
- We gotta go in tonight.
- Very funny.

14:46.261 --> 14:48.555
No, I'm serious.
We turn into a pumpkin tomorrow at noon.

14:48.931 --> 14:50.849
- The machines aren't ready.
- I know.

14:51.225 --> 14:52.559
I know, we gotta work faster.

14:52.684 --> 14:54.019
That, that's not possible.

14:54.186 --> 14:56.188
It's physically impossible, Marius.

14:56.271 --> 14:57.815
Finish the crate and wrap it.

14:58.941 --> 15:01.026
- And what's inside?
- Nothing.

15:03.028 --> 15:04.113
We move tonight...

15:06.156 --> 15:08.200
You have the casino manager to deal with.

15:08.784 --> 15:11.245
- You gonna put her in the crate?
- Katie's taking care of that.

15:11.370 --> 15:12.663
I thought she was out.

15:12.746 --> 15:14.665
She's doing a surprise guest performance.

15:14.748 --> 15:16.208
How's the water gag coming along?

15:16.250 --> 15:18.585
You want it done right
or do you want it done fast?

15:18.627 --> 15:20.838
- I want it done both.
- It's like telling Monet

15:20.921 --> 15:22.548
to hurry up with the water lilies.

15:23.048 --> 15:25.259
The bigger the pay-out,
the bigger the mistakes.

15:25.467 --> 15:27.970
You're letting all this money
just fuck up your head, son.

15:28.053 --> 15:29.721
Look, I know that I'm no con

15:30.013 --> 15:33.225
- but I also know that rushing is a mistake.
- Alright.

15:42.818 --> 15:43.694
Porter.

15:45.863 --> 15:49.491
Do you remember that wildcatter
we took down in East Texas?

15:49.867 --> 15:54.830
It was you, me, and the mark standing
in the middle of an empty oil field.

15:55.664 --> 16:00.210
We had 30 minutes of prep
and an oil can filled with ink

16:00.836 --> 16:02.796
and that was it.

16:03.255 --> 16:06.967
AJ, what about that safe we cracked
on Rodeo Drive?

16:07.551 --> 16:09.511
In the middle of the day
during operating hours.

16:10.596 --> 16:14.558
We we had no preparation,
but we took advantage of the opportunity.

16:16.310 --> 16:19.313
Pete, Gina, not-Bob...

16:20.564 --> 16:24.109
this is the job that I'll be referencing
the next time you guys have doubts.

16:24.443 --> 16:25.360
This is it.

16:28.489 --> 16:29.364
He's right.

16:32.159 --> 16:33.160
Let's make a crate.

16:33.911 --> 16:34.953
Wrap that shit.

16:35.037 --> 16:35.913
Let's go.

16:38.373 --> 16:39.625
You gotta pass this by Luka.

16:39.958 --> 16:41.126
He doesn't like surprises.

16:41.210 --> 16:43.754
- I'll explain it to him. He'll understand.
- Yeah.

16:46.548 --> 16:48.258
Abso-fucking-lutely not.

16:48.717 --> 16:49.801
Find other way.

16:52.971 --> 16:54.097
There is no other way.

16:54.389 --> 16:56.808
It's this or lose your $11 million.

17:00.354 --> 17:02.564
You think I forget?

17:03.607 --> 17:04.608
Forget what?

17:05.400 --> 17:06.443
You're a con man.

17:09.154 --> 17:10.030
Hm?

17:10.781 --> 17:11.657
This is a set-up.

17:12.074 --> 17:13.534
- Oh, no, no, no, no.
- Huh?

17:14.117 --> 17:16.620
You think you going to steal

17:16.662 --> 17:18.288
- my fucking money?
- No, I swear to God.

17:18.330 --> 17:20.165
- I swear to God, Luka.
- Luka!

17:20.624 --> 17:22.084
I was there when the call came in.

17:23.043 --> 17:26.046
This is not bullshit.
It's a real fucking problem.

17:30.884 --> 17:34.304
And how you know he is not playing you?

17:35.305 --> 17:36.807
Cos his team was caught off-guard.

17:38.100 --> 17:41.436
They're pissed off, fighting with him.
They don't wanna do it.

17:43.063 --> 17:44.398
They don't wanna do it?

17:45.941 --> 17:47.693
So how you gonna pull this off?

17:49.736 --> 17:51.488
Your team doesn't want to do it.

17:52.948 --> 17:54.783
- You.
- Me? What?

17:55.617 --> 17:57.953
They all know you, your reputation.

17:58.704 --> 17:59.788
They respect you.

18:00.289 --> 18:04.042
If you say go tonight,
they will go tonight.

18:13.302 --> 18:16.388
According to the sign, the bookworm
should've been open two hours ago.

18:18.015 --> 18:19.141
Maybe Pete warned her.

18:19.683 --> 18:21.560
You know, in case you came looking.

18:23.228 --> 18:24.354
You might be right.

18:28.692 --> 18:29.901
Taylor says I'm smart

18:30.736 --> 18:32.070
that I can do anything I want.

18:33.071 --> 18:35.699
I wanna do this,
what we're doing now.

18:35.907 --> 18:38.702
I wanna learn the bail bond business
and take down bad guys.

18:39.661 --> 18:43.624
- Carly...
- Mum did it, and she was good.

18:44.249 --> 18:45.250
Grandpa told me.

18:45.917 --> 18:46.918
I can be good too.

18:47.252 --> 18:49.963
That might be the only thing
that she passed down to me

18:50.047 --> 18:52.841
other than the vague facial resemblance
that I just don't see.

18:55.927 --> 18:58.138
Carly, it's not about
bringing down bad guys.

19:00.515 --> 19:02.267
Most of our clients are good people.

19:03.018 --> 19:05.771
They just made a mistake
and need some help.

19:06.271 --> 19:09.650
But sometimes, we get a chance
to ruin a bad guy's day.

19:14.029 --> 19:15.697
Ah... come on.

19:18.950 --> 19:20.035
Excuse me?

19:20.410 --> 19:21.870
I saw you delivering the mail.

19:22.412 --> 19:24.956
- You know the owner?
- I most certainly do.

19:25.082 --> 19:27.042
For whatever reason, I always get her mail.

19:27.167 --> 19:28.669
Oh, well, maybe you can help me.

19:29.211 --> 19:31.296
Um, my brother's a preacher

19:31.421 --> 19:33.840
has a little church near our home
in Stony Brook.

19:34.257 --> 19:35.509
Collects rare books.

19:35.801 --> 19:37.719
He's quite passionate
about it, right, Carly?

19:37.886 --> 19:39.304
Yeah, yeah, you should see his house.

19:39.388 --> 19:41.014
- Books everywhere.
- Yeah.

19:41.682 --> 19:45.352
I heard this store has
a rare Ben-Hur, 1860.

19:45.686 --> 19:49.231
Normally, they sell first editions,
but this is a third edition

19:49.314 --> 19:51.525
with the erratum on page 116.

19:51.733 --> 19:53.151
- Erratum?
- Oh...

19:53.902 --> 19:55.028
It's a printing error.

19:55.320 --> 19:57.030
I learned the term from my brother.

19:57.489 --> 19:59.908
And Carly wants to give it to him
as a birthday present.

20:00.158 --> 20:01.243
I've been saving up.

20:02.077 --> 20:04.413
Is there any chance
you might have her cellphone number?

20:05.080 --> 20:07.749
It's a long drive from Stony Brook
and I need to get her home

20:07.874 --> 20:10.836
- for cheerleading try-outs.
- No, Grandma, this is way more important.

20:10.877 --> 20:12.170
There's always next year. I...

20:12.379 --> 20:15.257
No, sure, but I can tell you where she is.

20:15.882 --> 20:17.676
Uh, today's her scavenge day.

20:17.759 --> 20:20.387
She goes to this indoor flea market
in Brooklyn

20:21.012 --> 20:23.140
on the corner of Hawthorne and Albany.

20:23.432 --> 20:25.684
- Oh, thank you so much.
- Sure.

20:28.562 --> 20:31.022
- Where did all that come from?
- Movie.

20:32.524 --> 20:35.152
- Wow, Grandma's good at this too.
- Mm-hmm.

20:38.196 --> 20:42.200
Tim, didn't we have an HVAC maintenance
inspection last year?

20:42.367 --> 20:44.619
- We did.
- Our company was bought out.

20:45.454 --> 20:48.081
The new boss is having us do these
once a year now.

20:48.749 --> 20:50.709
He's all about preventative maintenance.

20:51.334 --> 20:53.628
Get me Business Affairs.
